  "notes": "The top-level main skill is the user-facing actor: it selects ordered reviewers, owns foundation_gate and production_gate, and speaks in plain language. Domain Helper, Data Technician, Design Planner, and DAG Builder maintain foundation evaluator YAML records before foundation_gate. After foundation_gate opens, method/job subskills, Causal Discovery when graph support is needed, Data Technician, and Report Writer participate as production transition kernels through analysis.production_loop. Activated method/job and discovery subskills append compact records to subskill_analyses only when selected. Severe production findings can trigger return_to_foundation. Report Writer owns analysis.report_writer_20 and takes over final report synthesis only after production_gate is ready, using recorded foundation and production evidence rather than starting a new interaction loop. Canonical workflow enum values live in assets/workflow_enums.yaml. Canonical subskill metadata lives in this manifest; legacy per-subskill skill.json files are intentionally not used."
